%N A396749 Number of 2-ball multiplex prime juggling patterns of period n.
%C A396749 This sequence enumerates the exact count of prime multiplex juggling patterns of period n using 2 balls, where the hand capacity is at least 2.
%C A396749 A prime pattern is defined as a corresponding closed walk in the juggling state graph that visits n distinct states before returning to the start. The formula extends the methodology used for normal 2-ball prime patterns by introducing transition cards that represent simultaneous landings and crossings. For the sequence of normal 2-ball prime patterns, see A260744.
%H A396749 S. Butler, V. Choi, J. Jeffries, N. McCambridge, A. Morgenstern, and S. Orellana Mateo, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17284">Enumerating Prime Patterns in Juggling Variations</a>, arXiv:2603.17284 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A396749 Samuel Orellana Mateo, <a href="https://github.com/Samuel-O-M/prime-juggling-patterns">Prime Juggling Patterns Companion Code</a>, GitHub repository, 2026.
%F A396749 a(n) = Sum_{t>=1} ( c_t(n) + Sum_{m=1..n-1} t * c_t(m) ) + 1 where c_t(n) = h_t(n) / (t*(t+1)) and h_t(n) is defined by the recurrence h_t(n) = (t+1)*(h_{t-1}(n-t) + h_t(n-t)) with h_0(0) = 1, h_t(0) = h_0(n) = 0.
%F A396749 Asymptotically, a(n) ~ gamma * 2^n, where gamma = Sum_{t>=1} (t+1) * q_t, and q_t is defined by q_1 = 1/2 and q_t = ((t-1)/(2^t - t - 1)) * q_{t-1} for t >= 2.
%o A396749 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A396749 Cf. A260744, A260745, A260746, A260752.
